.TH "pin_request" 9 "pin_request" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pin_request \- request a single pin to be muxed in, typically for GPIO
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pin_request
.BI "(struct pinctrl_dev *pctldev "  ","
.BI "int pin "  ","
.BI "const char *owner "  ","
.BI "struct pinctrl_gpio_range *gpio_range "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pctldev" 12
the associated pin controller device
.IP "pin" 12
the pin number in the global pin space
.IP "owner" 12
a representation of the owner of this pin; typically the device
name that controls its mux function, or the requested GPIO name
.IP "gpio_range" 12
the range matching the GPIO pin if this is a request for a
single GPIO pin
